French President Francois Hollande on Saturday said he would visit Iraq on Monday to salute troops which are taking part in a U.S.-led military coalition against the Islamic State.&#8220;We&#8217;re not done with the plight of terrorism. We have to keep on fighting it,&#8221; Hollande said in a New Year address to the nation that was broadcast on French television.&#8220;This is the reason for our military operations abroad, in Mali, in Syria, in Iraq &#8212; Iraq where I&#8217;ll be going the day after tomorrow to salute our troops.&#8221;-Reuters